<p><span class="fw">1806</span>
</p>
<p>July</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">pell mell whipping and spurring their horses along the foot of the hill<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[A]</span>fter forming a long circuit they arrived full speed at the village<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Here they performed their warlike manoeveurs on horseback making attacks parrying the Strokes of the battle axe defending and covering themselves from arrows with their shields &amp;<sup>c</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Les Gros Ventres</span> instead of <span class="DelHand-author">amusing themselves at</span> these exercises amuse themselves by firing at marks.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">I observed that one game was in great vogue among the mandanes which the young men made their principal employment.  <span class="AddHand-editors">[T]</span>he party consists of two who are provided with sticks about six feet in length in which are cut a certain number of notches at proper distances<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  In the intervals are fixed an equal number of small bunches of feathers of divers colours all these have different meanings which those who can play only can understand<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[T]</span>he ground on which they play is a smooth level space about <span class="DelHand-author">40</span> <span class="AddHand-author">Forty</span> paces in length<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Both parties start together trotting until near half way when <span class="AddHand-author">the </span>one who is provided with a ball throws it ahead with sufficient force to reach the place allotted at the same time both</p>
<p style="text-align:right;">parties</p>

<p align="page-number"><span class="AddHand-editors">[47]</span></p>

